{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":23515,"name":"","username":"Florastamine","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/florastamine/{size}/272_2.png","created_at":"2018-03-04T16:15:42.429Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI have a mini-game for my game in which the player has to paint a lot of decals. The decals are randomly chosen from a pool of images. Problem is, a \u003ccode\u003eDecalSet\u003c/code\u003e can only hold a single decal material, and that left me creating a lot of \u003ccode\u003eDecalSet\u003c/code\u003e components whenever I want to paint a decal, because the decals are different and not using that same single material. Performance considerably dropped down.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e0 decal:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cimg src=\"//cdck-file-uploads-global.s3.dualstack.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/d/de81eedd7122a8f3b7f47a78236f28400743a8ec.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"690\" height=\"387\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e50+ decals, the time spent during \u003ccode\u003eRender/Present\u003c/code\u003e increased a lot:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cimg src=\"//cdck-file-uploads-global.s3.dualstack.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/5/50f602f19bbe9d4c061f09e12c652977e5f8ab23.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"690\" height=\"387\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIs there any workaround? I know I can customize \u003ccode\u003eDecalSet\u003c/code\u003e into something else, i.e. \u003ccode\u003eLightDecalSet\u003c/code\u003e which optimizes for only one decal, but I’d like to know what I’ve been missing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThank you!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-03-04T16:17:46.512Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":11,"reads":35,"readers_count":34,"score":62.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":4074,"topic_slug":"decalset-for-a-lot-of-decal-materials","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":699,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":23517,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2018-03-04T17:06:30.024Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eMaybe back them into the atlas?\u003cbr\u003e\nDo you \u003cem\u003ereally\u003c/em\u003e need multiple materials, or just multiple textures?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-03-04T17:06:30.024Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":35,"readers_count":34,"score":22.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":4074,"topic_slug":"decalset-for-a-lot-of-decal-materials","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":23518,"name":"Jonathan","username":"Sinoid","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/f19dbf/{size}.png","created_at":"2018-03-04T17:19:28.971Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eOr use a texture array if it’s just the textures you care about and tweak the shader so you can use \u003ca href=\"https://www.fxguide.com/featured/udim-uv-mapping/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eUDIM\u003c/a\u003e or your own convention.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eArrays are less hassle than texture atlases but do require all decals be the same resolution.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-03-04T17:19:28.971Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":34,"readers_count":33,"score":21.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":4074,"topic_slug":"decalset-for-a-lot-of-decal-materials","display_username":"Jonathan","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.fxguide.com/featured/udim-uv-mapping/","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"UDIM UV mapping | fxguide","clicks":13}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":669,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":23530,"name":"","username":"Florastamine","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/florastamine/{size}/272_2.png","created_at":"2018-03-05T13:49:12.783Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThank you both \u003ca class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/sinoid\"\u003e@Sinoid\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/eugene\"\u003e@Eugene\u003c/a\u003e for your suggestions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/eugene\"\u003e@Eugene\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\"\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDo you really need multiple materials, or just multiple textures?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYes, what I really want is multiple textures. But I totally forgot about using atlases, thank you! So I packed up all my textures with \u003ccode\u003eSpritePacker\u003c/code\u003e and manually specifying UV coords during \u003ccode\u003eDecalSet::AddDecal()\u003c/code\u003e to only paint what I need. That works wonderfully, and I don’t have to deal with having to create a crazy amount of \u003ccode\u003eDecalSet\u003c/code\u003e anymore.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cimg src=\"//cdck-file-uploads-global.s3.dualstack.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/2/2cfa97511c4e7c59fbec4441834797186a6952f5.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"412\" height=\"500\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt surely performs better than the last time, scoring 70+ fps with 90 decals, performance loss is minimal:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cimg src=\"//cdck-file-uploads-global.s3.dualstack.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/b/baf8dd401a675a3fb11b279308ea4587c9fefec4.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"690\" height=\"387\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/sinoid\"\u003e@Sinoid\u003c/a\u003e I digged the documentation and it seems like Urho has some sort of support for texture arrays (\u003ccode\u003eTexture2DArray\u003c/code\u003e), but I’m pretty confused on how to use it. Was it the texture array thingy you were talking about?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-03-05T13:49:12.783Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":28,"readers_count":27,"score":20.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":4074,"topic_slug":"decalset-for-a-lot-of-decal-materials","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":699,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":23531,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2018-03-05T14:07:16.775Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"4074\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/florastamine/40/272_1.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e Florastamine:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ebut I’m pretty confused on how to use it\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMake texture array resource combined of all needed textures.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMake custom shader that is able to sample these textures according to some ID\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSomehow pass this ID along with decal into DecalSet\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePros:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eNo edge bleeding issues\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCons:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHarder to maintain\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSame texture size for each texture\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-03-05T14:07:16.775Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":26,"readers_count":25,"score":25.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":4074,"topic_slug":"decalset-for-a-lot-of-decal-materials","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_ur